the entrepreneurs screening and panel discussion of the new camfed film the entrepreneurs screening and panel discussion of the new camfed film facebook twitter email print add to calendar in zambia in partnership with goldman sachs and the university of cambridge camfed launched the 10000 women program in young women's leadership and enterprise in 2008 a documentary film team led by helen cotton and academy award winner ross kaufmann chronicled this innovative program the first of its kind in zambia their uplifting documentary the entrepreneurs profiles young women participants florence esnart ng andwe and precious as they embark on five months of intensive training like all the young women in the course they come from backgrounds of extreme rural poverty and many suffered from the loss of one or both of their parents but with courage and determination these young women defy the odds and establish their own successful businesses from a furniture store to a pre school for vulnerable children the entrepreneurs prove that anything is possible panelists for the discussion include joel samoff professor of african studies and political science at stanford and kimberley sevcik information & media relations manager at camfed when tuesday march 8 2011 7 00 pm approximate duration of 2.0 hour s where building 380 room 380c 450 serra mall stanford ca map audience faculty staff general public students members tags film humanities public service other international arts sponsor clayman institute for gender research contact 725 0373 ann enthoven stanford edu admission free and open to all permalink http events stanford edu events 260 26007 more info last modified march 4 2011
